{{!--
  FDM passthrough post — for the **Creality Print environment**.

  WorkTrackCAM delegates real slicing to CuraEngine via src/main/slicer.ts;
  this post is invoked only when the CAM/Manufacture pipeline runs against
  an FDM machine (e.g., dry-runs, custom utility ops). It is intentionally
  minimal — it just emits the toolpath lines verbatim with a small header,
  so no CNC spindle/coolant macros leak into FDM output.

  Lines starting with ";" are operator-visible comments. Marlin/Klipper firmware
  treats ";" as a line comment.

  Template context keys: resources/posts/README.md (PostContext / renderPost).
--}}
